2:03 PM Prosecuting attorney Michael William Schiek in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Julian C. Schlottman appeared by video from the Dodge Correctional Institution, in custody. Victim appearing telephonically. Schiek statement to agreement. Plea Questionnaire has been presented. Defendant still wants to proceed on own. Court reads on waiver of counsel - waiver free and voluntary. Defendant waives right to in person appearance. Schiek statement to agreement. State moves to dismiss count 2. Granted. Defendant pleads no contest. Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Victim makes statement. Schiek/Defendant/Court statement to sentencing. 

Court Sentence;
WSP - 3 years - concurrent to current sentence;
Initial Incarceration - 1 year;
Extended Supervision - 2 years;
Jail Credit - 83 days;
Restitution - $610.00 + 10% totaling $671.00;
Costs are remitted;
DNA Sample;
The court informs defendant of right to request expunction of the DNA under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4).
Any other counseling/conditions deemed appropriate by PO;

Eligible for Substance Abuse Program;
Eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program;

Court explains appeal rights;

